	<section class="chapters">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
           
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\download.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 1 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 1: Arjuna Vishada Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">Arjuna is conflicted on the battlefield, torn between his duty as a warrior and his moral dilemma. He seeks guidance from Lord Krishna.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/1" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

           
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\1449-70.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 2 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 2: Sankhya Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">Lord Krishna imparts wisdom on the nature of the soul, duty, and emphasizing the importance of fulfilling one's duty without attachment to outcomes.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/2" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

           
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\download (2).jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 3: Karma Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text"> Krishna teaches the significance of performing one's duty selflessly and with dedication, emphasizing the importance of action without selfish desires.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/3" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\download (3).jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 4: Jgnana Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This chapter delves the relationship between knowledge, action, and renunciation, highlighting the necessity of aligning action with wisdom.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/4" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\meditation.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 5: Karma Sanyāsa Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">Lord Krishna explains the concept of renunciation, stressing that true renunciation is not mere abandonment of action but detachment from desires and ego.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/5" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\x976442_Jnana,P20Yoga.jpg.pagespeed.ic.ecliA8aOF_.webp" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 6: Dhyāna Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This chapter elucidates the practice of meditation, focusing on achieving a balanced and disciplined mind through yogic practices.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/6" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\krishna-arjuna.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 7: Vignana Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This explains the difference between the divine and demonic qualities and emphasizes the importance of seeking true knowledge to attain spiritual liberation.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/7" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\devotee praying.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 8: Akṣhara Parabrahma Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This chapter explores the nature of the eternal, imperishable reality and the process of attaining union with it through devotion and meditation.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/8" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\744.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 9: Rāja Vidyā Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">In this Krishna reveals the profound knowledge of devotion, emphasizing the supreme and confidential wisdom of spiritual realization.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/9" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\1_IwlN7l8uBnXltYxOFfAiFQ.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 10: Vibhūti Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text"> Krishna describes His divine manifestations and explains the limitless manifestations of His power and opulence in the world.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/10" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\download (1).jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 11: Viśhwarūpa Sandarśhana Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">Arjuna is granted a divine vision of Lord Krishna's universal form, revealing the cosmic grandeur and omnipresence of the Supreme.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/11" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\Bhaktiyoga_813b32d6-30b9-4af4-8806-82213747593d.webp" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 12 : Bhakthi Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This chapter focuses on the significance of devotion and surrender to God, elaborating on different forms of spiritual practice and their merits.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/12" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\unnamed.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 13: Kṣhetra Kṣhetrajña Vibhāga Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text"> Krishna explains the distinction between the physical body and the soul , elucidating the nature of the material and spiritual worlds.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/13" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\Lord-Krishna-and-Arjuna-1.webp" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 14: Guṇa Traya Vibhāga Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">The three gunas (qualities) - sattva (goodness), rajas (passion), and tamas (ignorance), and their influence on human behavior and spiritual evolution.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/14" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\Gita15_800.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 15: Puruṣhottama Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This chapter describes the eternal and transcendental nature of the Supreme Being, illustrating the metaphor of the eternal tree of life.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/15" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\images.jpeg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 16: Daivāsura Sampad Vibhāga Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">In this Krishna elaborates on the divine and demonic qualities within individuals and their influence on one's actions.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/16" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\sculpture-wood-statue-krishna-arjuna-35.webp" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 17: Śhraddhā Traya Vibhāga Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">In this lordKrishna discusses the different types of faith and their corresponding actions, elucidating the importance of faith in spiritual practices.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/16" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			
			
			<div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card" style="width: 250px;">
                    <img src="images\Gita18.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Chapter 3 Image" style="height: 200px; object-fit: cover;">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h3 class="card-title">Chapter 18: Moksha Sansaya Yoga</h3>
                        <p class="card-text">This final chapter addresses renunciation, duty, and liberation, guiding individuals on the path towards spiritual enlightenment and ultimate freedom.</p>
                        <a href="https://bhagavadgita.io/chapter/18" class="btn btn-primary">Know More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            

        </div>
    </div>
